{"title":"SVI Heat Maps text","type":"markdown","params":{"fontSize":12,"openLinksInNewTab":false,"markdown":"# Heat Maps
Heat maps can be used to help tease out relationships between variables within the SVI and ACS data with respect to call volume.

- Bottom Left: A heat map displaying call volume as a function of both Per Capita Income and  % Non-white Population

- Bottom Right: A heat map displaying call volume as a function of % of population living with a disability and % of population over the age of 65. Can be used to determine whether there are any anomalies in reaching especially vulnerable older/disabled populations"},"aggs":[]}
